<br>
As a 55 mage, the 2 SoL (until the now nerfed focus items) spells I currently have and can use are:<br>
<br>
1. Veil of Elements--improved invis, which Enchanters, Necromancers, and Wizards all had before SoL<br>
<br>
2. A new pet heal that costs almost as much mana as a new pet and heals the pet approx 25%.  <br>
<br>
If I am lucky to find someone selling the new mod rod when I hit 56, I will have my ability to give others my mana more efficiently.  <br>
<br>
At 58 I will be able to regen mana a 3/tick without the help of any spells or gear.  Dear God I can feel the power of the magi.<br>
<br>
Now, as to the focus items creating imbalance, they didn't as orginally implemented.  All casters could benefit from them, and the improvements in caster damage were not such that casters would still anyone's thunder.  I still believe the issue is that everyone could use them, not just &quot;ubers.&quot;  <br>
<br>
The idea that anything summoned could be good seems to upset some people.  Well as a mage I would like to think that my summon spells have some use as that and the pet are what lead me to play a mage in the first place.  It sounded fun.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I cannot imagine playing another class and enjoying it as much as I enjoy my mage, but please do not tell me that we are balanced; we are not.<br>
